>>>>> Trent Arsenault writes:
 > Now that kernel 2.3.39 and beyond support  32-bit UID numbers, does anyone 
 > know if there is any plan to build high UID support into future glibc 2 
 > releases?
 > I've seen unofficial 32-bit UID patches for glibc 2 but nothing in the 
 > latest development releases of glibc 2 to support 32-bit UIDs.
You seem to have overlooked them.
The development version of glibc 2.2 has (nearly [1]) all the support
in.  Porting those patches back for glibc 2.1.3 isn't going to happen
since the patches changed quite a lot and need further testing.
Andreas
Footnotes: 
[1]  Some patches still need to be applied.
